# Output Convergence Plan

## Vision
Commands become pure data producers returning structured data. The framework
selects a rendering template based on flags (--json, TTY detection). Commands
never call writeJson or stdout.write directly.

## Two output forms in buildCommand
1. `"json"` — flag injection only, command handles own output
2. `{ json: true, human: fn }` — full auto-render with { data, hint? } return

## Phased rollout

### Phase 1 (merged in #382): Core infrastructure + Tier 1 commands
- OutputConfig<T> on buildCommand with human/json/jsonExclude
- CommandOutput<T> return type ({ data, hint? })
- OutputError for non-zero exit with output data
- Converted: event/view, issue/view, issue/explain, issue/plan, org/view

### Phase 2 (this PR): Tier 2-3 commands
- Return-based: project/view, log/view, org/list, trace/list
- jsonTransform on OutputConfig for custom JSON envelopes
- Consola: auth/login, logout, status, cli/feedback, setup, fix, upgrade, api.ts
- Removed stderr: Writer threading from api.ts helpers

### Phase 3 (future): Streaming list commands
- Convert issue/list, project/list, log/list (complex dispatch + pagination)
- Potential buildStreamingCommand with JSONL output
- Follow-mode stderr.write in log/list

### Phase 4 (future): Final cleanup
- Remove remaining direct stdout/stderr/writeJson usage
- Add lint rule to prevent regression
- interactive-login.ts conversion (separate PR)

## Intentionally preserved
- auth/token: stdout.write for pipe capture (| pbcopy)
- interactive-login.ts: 15+ writes, deeply coupled, separate PR
